<frame name="FR_Grant_permission-Permitting" ID="10068" xsi:schemaLocation="../schema/frame.xsd" xmlns="http://framenet.icsi.berkeley.edu" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" domains="Verbal_communication">
    <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;In this frame either a &lt;fen&gt;Grantor&lt;/fen&gt; (a person or an institution) or a &lt;fen&gt;Principle&lt;/fen&gt; (either moral or legal) grants or denies permission for a &lt;fen&gt;Grantee&lt;/fen&gt; to perform an &lt;fen&gt;Action&lt;/fen&gt; or for an &lt;fen&gt;Action&lt;/fen&gt; to occur. 

&lt;ex&gt; &lt;fex name="Grantor"&gt;My mother&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;let&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Grantee"&gt;me&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;fex name="Action"&gt;go to the movies with Simon&lt;/fex&gt; . &lt;/ex&gt; 

&lt;ex&gt; &lt;fex name="Grantor"&gt;The teacher&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;m&gt;gave&lt;/m&gt; &lt;fex name="Grantee"&gt;the children&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;permission&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Action"&gt;to eat their lunch outside&lt;/fex&gt;. &lt;/ex&gt;

&lt;ex&gt; &lt;fex name="Principle"&gt;Code 1425&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;allows&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Grantee"&gt;us&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;fex name="Action"&gt;to deduct interest payments&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;asf&gt;Relation to fndata-1.5&lt;/asf&gt; : Merge of Grant_permission with Deny_permission (cf. no reason to specify an Authority in Deny_permission frame, and a Grantor in Grant_permission frame). Also merged with the Permitting and Prohibiting frames, the difference between a human Grantor versus a Principle providing or denying some authorization is made at the level of FEs. Note this possibility exists both for authorization and denial, which is a further reason to merge all the four frames. The verbs which do not take a Grantee indirect object are better coped with in the Ratification or FR_Taking_sides frames (see FR: approuver (EN: approve))
&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    <FE bgColor="FF0000" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="296" cDate="01/17/2003 01:22:01 PST Fri" abbrev="Gro" name="Grantor" ID="4076">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The &lt;fen&gt;Grantor&lt;/fen&gt; is the individual or group of individuals or institution vested with the authority to grant permission with respect to a specific domain and who grants permission to the &lt;fen&gt;Grantee&lt;/fen&gt;.&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
        <semType name="Sentient" ID="5"/>
	<excludesFE name="Principle" ID="4092"/>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="00BFFF" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="296" cDate="01/20/2003 01:06:58 PST Mon" abbrev="Prin" name="Principle" ID="4092">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The &lt;fen&gt;Principle&lt;/fen&gt; is the code or authority which permits the &lt;fen&gt;Action&lt;/fen&gt;.&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
	<excludesFE name="Grantor" ID="4076"/>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="0000FF" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="296" cDate="01/17/2003 01:29:08 PST Fri" abbrev="Gre" name="Grantee" ID="4077">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The &lt;fen&gt;Grantee&lt;/fen&gt; is the individual who is given permission to engage in a certain &lt;fen&gt;Action&lt;/fen&gt;.&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
        <semType name="Sentient" ID="5"/>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="2E8B57" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="296" cDate="01/17/2003 01:29:52 PST Fri" abbrev="Act" name="Action" ID="4078">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The &lt;fen&gt;Action&lt;/fen&gt; is the activity of the &lt;fen&gt;Grantee&lt;/fen&gt; that the &lt;fen&gt;Grantor&lt;/fen&gt; permits.&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    </FE>
